   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Ninety-three JESUS BORE OUR SINS Scripture: Gal 3:13b; 1 Pet 2:24 Jesus was hanged upon the tree Jesus was hanged upon the tree; that is, Jesus was crucified on the cross.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Crucifixion was a death penalty during the days of the Roman Empire.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>When Jesus was crucified on the cross, He was suffering the death penalty.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Jesus Himself bore our sins Jesus suffered the death penalty not because He was sinful, but because He bore our sins.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>As Jesus was dying on the cross, God put all our sins upon Him.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Jesus crucifixion was the way ordained by God to deal with our sins.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>During Jesus crucifixion on the cross, the heavens and the earth were darkened.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>This signifies that Jesus was forsaken by God when He bore our sins upon the cross.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The results of Jesus bearing our sins Now we can have our sins forgiven Now we can be justified by God.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Now we can obtain the life of God.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>How to partake of the sin-bearing Jesus</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Develop this point.</S>
   </TEXT>
